recipes.strInstructions: To prepare feijoada, start by desalting the dried beef, soaking it in water for at least 12 hours and changing the water several times. After desalting, drain and cut the beef into pieces. Next, boil the meats (dried beef, pork, and sausages) for a few minutes to reduce the salt content. Drain and set aside. Wash the black beans thoroughly and cook them in a pressure cooker with water, bringing it to pressure for about 15 minutes, and then turning off the heat to release the pressure naturally. In a separate large pot, sauté chopped onions and garlic in oil until they are golden brown. Add the prepared meats and sauté for a few more minutes. Transfer this mixture to the pot of cooked beans, add bay leaves, and simmer over medium-low heat for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally and adding hot water as needed, until the meats are tender and the beans have thickened the broth. Season with salt and black pepper to taste, remove the bay leaves, and serve the feijoada hot, accompanied by cooked rice, sautéed collard greens, cassava flour, and, if desired, pork cracklings (torresmo) and chopped cilantro and green onions.

recipes.strInstructions: To make simple vanilla ice cream, combine 2 cups of heavy cream and 1 cup of whole milk in a bowl, ensuring they're well mixed. Add 3/4 cup of granulated sugar and stir until fully dissolved. Incorporate 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract, adjusting to taste. Transfer the mixture into an ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer's guidelines to churn it for around 20-25 minutes until it's soft and creamy. You can include extras like chocolate chips or fruit pieces during the last minutes of churning. After achieving the desired consistency, either enjoy the ice cream as soft serve or transfer it to a container for a firmer texture. For a firmer consistency, place the container in the freezer for a few hours. If you lack an ice cream maker, freeze the mixture in a lidded container, stirring every 30 minutes to break up ice crystals and attain a smoother texture.

Preheat your grill or stovetop pan over medium-high heat. Divide 1 pound (450g) ground beef into 4 portions, shape them into patties slightly larger than the buns (they'll shrink while cooking), and season with salt and pepper. Cook the patties for 3-5 minutes per side based on your preferred doneness, adding cheese during the last minute if desired. Toast the hamburger buns. Assemble burgers by placing patties on the bottom bun halves, adding toppings like lettuce, tomato, onion, ketchup, and mayo, then topping with the other bun halves. Serve and enjoy!

In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt 2 tablespoons of butter with 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add thin strips of 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cooking until no longer pink; set aside. In the same skillet, cook chopped onion until translucent, then add minced garlic and sliced mushrooms, cooking until mushrooms are tender. Sprinkle in 1 tablespoon of flour, stir, pour in 1 cup of chicken broth, and simmer to thicken. Stir in 1 tablespoon of Dijon mustard and 1 tablespoon of tomato paste. Lower heat, return chicken to skillet, add 1/2 cup of sour cream gradually, and heat through. Season with salt and pepper, then serve over cooked rice or egg noodles. Garnish with parsley.
recipes.strIngredient1: boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into thin strips
recipes.strIngredient14: Cooked rice or egg noodles, for serving

recipes.strInstructions:
Finely chop 12 oz (340 g) of high-quality beef tenderloin and refrigerate. In a bowl, mix 2 egg yolks, 2 tsp Dijon mustard, 1 tbsp chopped capers, 1 tbsp chopped cornichons, small red onion, minced garlic, 2 tsp Worcestershire sauce, and 1 tsp hot sauce. Gently fold in the minced beef. Season with salt and pepper. Shape portions with a mold. Garnish with parsley. Serve with toasted bread. Consume immediately.

Please be aware of the raw meat and egg consumption, considering health concerns and dietary restrictions.
recipes.strIngredient10: Salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste
recipes.strIngredient12: Toasted bread or baguette slices, for serving

recipes.strInstructions: Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Place chicken breasts between sheets of plastic wrap, gently pound to 1/2 inch thickness. Season with salt and pepper. Set up breading station: coat chicken in flour, dip in beaten eggs, press into breadcrumb mixture. Heat 1/4 inch olive oil in skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken until golden (3-4 mins/side). Drain on paper towels. Spread thin layer of marinara sauce in baking dish, add chicken, top with more sauce and shredded mozzarella. Bake 15-20 mins at 375°F until cheese melts. Rest before serving. Garnish with basil. Serve over cooked spaghetti.
